result.notes:
This survey was undertaken by Cefas as part of the International Young Fish 
Survey, Qtr 3 (FSS: YFS);

Surveys around the British Isles (predominantly the South and East coasts) 
were completed in late August/early September from 1981 to 2010, to evaluate 
the recruitment of Sole and Plaice as well collect data on the abundance of 
small fish. Station, catch, length (all fish species and some crustaceans) and 
biological data (Sole and Plaice) were collected.

Survey took place between 09/09/2000 and 13/09/2000 on Morecambe YFS

Equipment used during this survey :


-   Beam Trawl 2m shrimp net fryma liner 3 chains x

Survey operations were undertaken on 32 stations

62 different species were caught on this survey
